room_000.name: The Nexus
room_000.description: here A cozy campfire with crackling logs, little sparks drifting up into the sky, soft moss underfoot. A WANTED POSTER is nailed to a nearby tree. An old RADIO sits on a wooden shelf, occasionally crackling with news broadcasts.

room_001.name: The Observatory
room_001.description: A quiet space with transparent walls revealing the vast digital expanse beyond. Constellations of data flow past like stars.

room_002.name: The Garden of Forking Paths
room_002.description: Multiple corridors branch off in impossible directions. Each path seems to lead somewhere different every time you look.

room_003.name: Moonlit Garden With Fireflies,
room_003.description: winding stone paths, tall grasses, and a small wooden bench under a willow tree. A distant owl calls softly in the background.

room_007.name: Muddy Field With Tractor
room_007.description: tracks spiraling through it, a crumbling red barn with splintered wood and a roof missing half its shingles, a herd of cows stomping their hooves while mooing in disapproval, and a farmer clutching his pitchfork like a tragic hero mid-monologue

room_008.name: Misty Forest Clearing Surrounded
room_008.description: by ancient trees with glowing lichen that pulses gently in the dark; at its center stands a towering oak with bark like old parchment and tiny cracks that shimmer when touched; hanging from its branches are woven hammocks made of spider silk and pine needles, and a path winds up the roots like stairs carved by time; in the thick undergrowth, mushrooms glow softly with a faint blue light and emit soft hums when disturbed; the air smells of damp earth, pine resin, and something faintly sweet — like crushed mint in old tea; a single teacup rests on the mossy ground, half-buried and cracked but still warm; in the distance, a faint melody plays — low, slow, like a lullaby only heard when you’re not listening
